<div class="postcell post-layout--right">
    
    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
                
<p>I don't really understand the <a href="https://github.com/tautologistics/node-htmlparser/" rel="nofollow">readme of htmlparser</a>.. and I searched over the internet but cannot find a proper tutorial for it (or other NodeJS parsers).</p>

<p>I believe for most of the time if there's no tutorial for a pretty complete and old library it's mostly because that it's easy to do thus people don't really feel the need to write tutorial for it... But I found NodeJS html parser is pretty hard to understand...</p>
    </div>

